{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large bowl on mixing bowl lid, weigh in spinach then set aside.","Place garlic, leeks, parsley and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add chorizo and sauté <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add passata, tomato purée, paprika, herbs, salt and pepper then cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add chicken, mix with spatula then cook <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with spinach, mix well with spatula then set aside to cool for 30 minutes.","Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 200°C and spray a springform tin (Ø 20 cm) with oil.","Line prepared tin with filo pastry sheets to cover base, with plenty of overhang around the edge, spraying each sheet with more oil after placing in tin. Spoon in cooled filling using a slotted spoon then fold overhanging pastry back into centre, scrunching together to enclose filling. Spray top with oil then bake for 35 minutes (200°C), covering with foil after 10-15 minutes if browning too much.","Carefully remove from tin and serve warm, in slices, with salad."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g fresh baby spinach","2 garlic cloves","300 g leeks, cut in pieces (5 cm)","5 g fresh parsley leaves","15 g olive oil","150 g chorizo, thinly sliced","100 g passata","2 Tbsp tomato purée","1 tsp smoked paprika","1 tsp dried mixed herbs","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","650 g chicken breast fillets, skinless, cut in pieces (2 cm)","cooking spray, any oil","5 filo pastry sheets","salad leaves, for serving"]}],"id":"r424072","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Yzd6Y854Vd8\/XZQF7V0BTEI\/AAAAAAAAb4M\/jXknCJf2CdwV0ORhKTmQtP7oqAedr9DZACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DzSq2p7A6SP2Orfm.png","title":"Chicken and Chorizo Filo Pie","publishedAt":"2019-01-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26 g","calories":"1447 kJ \/ 344 kcal"},"usefulItems":"aluminium foil, large bowl, slotted spoon, springform tin (Ø 20 cm), oven","basicInfo":["easy","35m","2h","6 portions"]}